Also: matmul_f16_pair_tensor is just two matmul_f16 calls; could be fused (single weight read for both projections share the same x). Worth measuring after the per-call kernel improvements land — pair calls are at 4096x256 mostly, 60 calls/tok = 1.9 ms/tok in the bundle. Saving the 2x x-read is small (x is in cache for the second call) but saving the launch is part of what graph capture would have done. Probably 0.5 ms/tok upside if fused properly.